text: Hello, I am on a shopify store, I have an embeded HubSpot form and I'm trying to automplete one of its inputs with Google API Places. The script loads, and it works if I press "down" arrow, the input gets autocompleted but the dropdown won't show. I tried it on a different input of that page, outside the form and it works completely fine. The error I get in the console is "InvalidValueError: not an instance of HTMLInputElement". Does anyone encountered this issue before?

Is it possible that you are trying to attach a listener to the form before its finished loading?  My initial guess is you'd want to listen for the onFormReady event <https://legacydocs.HubSpot.com/global-form-events>
